What is becoming a more common occurrence police say is the presence of fentanyl one of the deadliest opiates on the market.
Fentanyl is so deadly Wright said that in powder form the equivalent of two grains of salt added to opioids is a guaranteed overdose.
If you use drugs that are laced with fentanyl if you use fentanyl you will die Wright said.
The uptick of overdose deaths has triggered a collaborative response from the Memphis police the Shelby County Health Department and the Memphis Area Prevention Coalition who are all collaborating to combat the uptick in deaths by pushing resources into the public's hands.
Officials from all agencies stressed to the media on Friday the importance of addicts not using alone. Further Wright said if someone is abusing opioids the chances of an overdose death increase exponentially if they are alone.
Further Wright said having training and a supply of Narcan an overdose-reversal drug can increase your odds of survival should you overdose.
If you have a family member or you are a user of opiods you need to get trained on Narcan Wright said.
Currently 1379 Memphis police officer are trained and carry Narcan.
