MEMPHIS TN WMC - A Memphis man caught on video and ridiculed by witnesses during a heroin overdose sought help and is now speaking out about his recovery.
After 40 years of drug and alcohol addiction Ron Hiers is now drug free and opening up about the low moment that made him decide to get help.
Heirs 61 said he was in a Walgreens bathroom with his wife shooting up heroin just before they passed out on a sidewalk. A passerby went live on Facebook showing the scene where people laughed and took pictures of the couple who was obviously in desperate need of help.
The last thing I remember was walking out of Walgreens Hiers said. The public humiliation that my family had suffered mine being broadcast throughout the country and the world.
Hiers credits the man who published that video for saving his life. His daughter who lives out of state saw the video and quickly got her father enrolled at Turning Point treatment center.
He was in pretty bad shape Brian Sullivan Turning Point said. Our medical team took him straight in worked on him and kept a close eye on his vitals.
Hiers was in treatment for nearly two months. Now he is clean and taking life one day at a time.
It'll be a lifetime battle for me but it gets easier he said. It's like grieving for a loved one that's passed.
Hiers wife is also being treated but she is hundreds of miles away on the east coast.
There are places you can go and get help. And if you don't you might not see Christmas he said to anyone who is battling addiction.
Ron Hiers' lifetime of addiction reached a turning point and now looks ahead with hope of a new beginning.
If you or someone you love needs help breaking an addiction please call 1-888-614-2251. You can also visit Turning Point for more information.
