Fatal overdoses in Shelby County remain in the hundreds every year and recently finalized data from the Tennessee Department of Health shows that fentanyl continues to be a major driver of those fatalities. And non-fatal overdoses are still happening by thousands every year in Shelby County.
In 2021 549 people died after fatally overdosing on a substance and an additional 3111 overdose events were recorded by hospitals in Shelby County.
Fentanyl is now the leading drug behind fatal overdoses according to the Tennessee Department of Health.
