Over time West wrote members of the Memphis Mafia began to notice that Presleys drug use went beyond the typical partying associated with the rock and roll lifestyle. He alleged that Presley began to doctor-shop for various pills which could sometimes make the usually friendly gregarious and warm singer become impulsive mercurial and wildly unpredictable.
One evening West took Judy Alden an actress he was casually dating to a party at one of Presleys homes on Bellagio Road in Los Angeles.
Presley was shooting pool with the guys as usual when West walked in with his date. But he could tell that the singer wasnt his normal self. He seemed cold aloof and put out. West said Presley grew increasingly frustrated during a game of eight ball as he missed a lot of easy shots he normally would have made.
